Review Text: bought nearly four months ago buy new computer older hp spectre 360 longer updating properly started looking lenova yoga book love price back order tried wait research computers more almost got spectre it good computer finally another update spectre unworkable could wait get new computer needed one urgently best way it least looked lenova much saw far come love design ease use also really love oled screens computer issue sometimes fingerprint log work one night matter would let in also could get password work became quite worried indeed hard restart worked fine never happened again iit update recently since issues logging fingerprint otherwise fast turn go issues work applications citrix like lenovas set up like pen comes really wish way attaching computer prior versions appeared pocket afraid loosing keep using leaving home think find way attach even could used computer casei computer tech person know good basic knowledge get basic computer issues going get computer lingo work health care chart forever various remote desktops perhaps video telemedthis computer job also fun use work still going buy portable monitor make travel work easier glad purchased one battery live average hoped would longer certainly workable far new lenovo fan
Review Text Original: Bought this nearly four months ago. I only had to buy a new computer because my older HP Spectre 360 was no longer updating properly. I started looking at Lenova Yoga Book but did not love the price and it was on back order. I tried to wait and research computers more. Almost got the Spectre again (it was a good computer). Then finally another update and my Spectre was just about unworkable and could not wait to get new computer. I then needed one urgently which is not the best way to do it. I had at least looked at the Lenova so much and I saw how far they have come. I love the design and ease of use. I also really love the OLED screens on the computer. The only issue I have had is sometimes the fingerprint log in does not work. One night no matter what I did it would not let me in. I also could not get my password to work. I became quite worried indeed but after hard restart it worked fine and has never happened again. IIt had an update recently and since then not had issues logging in with fingerprint. Otherwise, it has been very fast turn on and go. No issues with my work applications (citrix). I like Lenova"s set up. I like the pen that comes with it but i really wish they had a way of attaching to computer, prior versions appeared to have a pocket. I am so afraid of loosing it that I keep not using it and leaving it at home. I think they should find a way to attach even if it could only be used while not in computer case.I am not a computer tech person. I know have good basic knowledge and get myself out of some basic computer issues but am not going to get into computer lingo. If you work in health care and have to chart forever on various remote desktops or perhaps do video telemed-this computer will do the job and also be fun to use when not doing such work. I am still going to buy a portable monitor to make travel work easier but am glad I purchased this one. The battery live is average. I had hoped it would be longer, but it is certainly workable.  I am so far a new Lenovo fan.
Description Original: The person likes the ease of use of this laptop

Charger is easily portable so not the biggest issue for me. fingerprint reader is handy, i do wish it would also do face recognition but NBD. Overall, i^m really happy with my purchase and impressed with Samsung.

Review Text: recently terrible experience samsung makes question continue buy products specifically bought earlier model np950qdbkb1us samsung galaxy book pro 360 15 approximately 2 years ago issues month ago forced bios update computerthe screen froze update showing progress day forced shut unable restart screen stayed black blinking blue light keyboard backlight show signs lifei literally viewed tried every suggested fix provided samsung support avail laptop warranty fine sending laptop repair estimate hopeful next step basically repair motherboard replacement charge 867 bucks politely requested rep see samsung could offer discount given barely laptop 2 years issue appeared caused samsung updatelong story short  discount ability speak manager nothing im buying new laptop 2 years spending quality bucks top line samsung product worried samsung products tvs tablets phones etc probably spend serious money samsungif highpriced product day warranty please beware
Description: new replace old one screen froze
Annotated Text: I bought a new laptop in 2
Review Text Original: {'Recently had a terrible experience with Samsung that makes me question if I will continue to buy its products. More specifically, I bought an earlier model (NP950QDB-KB1US) Samsung Galaxy Book Pro 360 15" approximately 2 years ago and had no issues until about a month ago when it forced a BIOS update on the computer.The screen froze during the update showing no progress for over a day. I forced shut off and was unable to restart. The screen stayed black, but I had the blinking blue light and the keyboard backlight show signs of life.I literally viewed and tried every suggested fix provided by Samsung support to no avail. The laptop was out of warranty, but I was fine sending the laptop for a repair estimate as a hopeful next step. Basically, the repair was a motherboard replacement with a charge of $867 bucks! I politely requested the rep to see if Samsung could offer me a discount given that the I barely had the laptop 2 years and the issue appeared to be caused by a Samsung update.Long story short - no discount, no ability to speak with a manager, no nothing. I"m buying a new laptop in 2 years after spending quality bucks on a top line Samsung product. I now am worried about all of my other Samsung products (TVs, tablets, phones, etc.). Probably will be a while before I spend serious money with Samsung.If your high-priced product is a day out of warranty, please beware!'}
Description Original: The user bought a new laptop to replace the old one after its screen froze

Review Text: galaxy book2 pro 360 156 screen beautiful looking laptop purchased replace almost 10 year old 17 touchscreen dell still looks brand new longer supported windows 81 treat electronics correctly normally get years use them used numerous samsung galaxy phones love them including latest s22 ultra we traded note 8 phones still pristine getting book2 home used sparingly sitting table could see crack screen way left right crack almost invisible mainly seen looking top screen laptop starts correctly screen looks bright clear except faint line crack know crack bought it cracked opening laptop use it course past return window looking online appears happened often enough now laptop still usable afraid screen completely unusable looking forward extremely expensive paperweight pay repair something cause
Review Text Original: This Galaxy Book2 Pro 360 15.6" screen is a beautiful looking laptop. It was purchased to replace our almost 10 year old 17" touchscreen Dell that still looks brand new but is no longer supported because of windows 8.1. We treat our electronics correctly, and normally get years of use out of them. We have used numerous Samsung Galaxy phones and love them, including our latest S22 Ultra. (We traded in our Note 8 phones that were still pristine) After getting the Book2 home, and it being used sparingly while sitting on the table, we could see the crack on the screen all the way from the left to the right. The crack is almost invisible, mainly seen when looking from the top of the screen. The laptop starts up correctly and the screen looks bright and clear, except for the faint line from the crack. We do not know if the crack was there when we bought it, or if it cracked on opening the laptop to use it. Of course it is past the return window. And now after looking online, it appears this has happened often enough. As of now, the laptop is still usable, but we are afraid the screen will completely be unusable. Not looking forward to an extremely expensive paperweight, or to have to pay to repair something we did not cause.
Description Original: The person dont like that this laptops screen cracked while using it
